            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The reason I use `vim.deprecate` in `_get_offset_encoding()` is that, although there is a plan to remove this function, it cannot be removed at the moment because we need it to maintain compatibility for `offset_encoding` being able to be `nil`. It should only be removed when this compatibility is no longer needed (i.e., after 0.12). Deprecate is appropriate in this context and can also serve as a reminder to remove it in the future.\r\n\r\nHowever, if no one agrees with the two ideas, I will modify this PR later to:\r\n* Do not deprecate `vim.lsp._get_offset_encoding()`\r\n* Keep the order of `make_*_params` parameters",
