        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> , it cannot be removed at the moment because we need it to maintain compatibility for offset_encoding being able to be nil.\r\n\r\nNo we don't. Underscore explicitly means \"no guarantees, behavior can change any time and the function may be removed\". Only documented functions need to be stable. (In this sense, the helper is an implementation detail and can be changed, inlined, made local, whatever.)",
            "created_at": "2024-11-18T11:51:16Z",
