        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "For `make_range_params` the win argument is kinda required - especially if you make follow up requests which can be async, and where the window might have changed. So freezing the window to a concrete number is the recommended practice.\r\nFlipping the order to allow leaving it off would only further advocate a bad pattern.\r\nAs for `make_given_range_params` - we should re-visit that anyway once we've a pos/range abstraction. Doing something now about it would likely just lead to more unnecessary churn. There's no acute pain-point this would fix.\r\n\r\nSuggestion to move forward with this:\r\n\r\n- Change the type annotations to indicate that the parameters are required\r\n- Show a message using notify_once if `offset_encoding` is missing\r\n\r\n\r\nDon't want to cause plugin authors who already use the methods in the correct way additional work. We've a good deal of deprecations/breaking changes already, no need to pile on more for some mostly cosmetic changes.\r\n",
